<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17077] When rejoining shard leader election, we try to leave the election twice</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17077</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When rejoining leader election, we tries to delete the leader election twice in Zookeeper.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This has no impact on the outcome of the leader election and this does not cause other failure. This is visible in logs (see bellow).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Sc&#233;nario details&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Method &lt;tt&gt;ZkController.rejoinShardLeaderElection()&lt;/tt&gt; leaves the election by removing the sequential election node and the leader registration node. This is done directly from there by invoking &lt;tt&gt;prevContext.cancelElection()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then &lt;tt&gt;LeaderElector.retryElection()&lt;/tt&gt; does that again (this.context.cancelElection()) but the second time around always fails as the Zookeeper nodes were already removed by the first attempt.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Following log line is logged each time we invoke &lt;tt&gt;REJOINELECTION&lt;/tt&gt; of a shard.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;em&gt;&quot;No version found for ephemeral leader parent node, won&apos;t remove previous leader registration.&quot;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
