&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17077&quot; title=&quot;When rejoining shard leader election, we try to leave the election twice&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-17077&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-17077&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: Don&apos;t cancel twice when rejoining shard leader election (#2084)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When a shard rejoins leader election, leave previous election only once to save unneeded calls to Zookeeper.  The prior behavior was noisy and less efficient; a bug perhaps albeit without real consequence.&lt;/p&gt;

